Subject: P versus NP Problem Space

& [ProblemSpace] is formal mathematical framing
  + [domain] is theoretical computer science and computational complexity
  + [core_objects] are decision problems, deterministic polynomial time, nondeterministic polynomial time, verifiers, certificates, reductions, and complexity classes P and NP
  + [central_question] is whether every decision problem whose solution can be verified in polynomial time can also be solved in polynomial time
  + [official_status] is open as of 2026-06-26 according to Clay Mathematics Institute public Millennium Problems framing
  + [authority_floor] is precise machine model, complexity definitions, reduction framework, and proof separating or equating P and NP

& [Delineation] is the problem boundary
  + [inside] is equality or inequality of P and NP for decision problems under standard complexity definitions
  + [boundary] is relation between efficient verification and efficient construction/search
  + [outside] is digit-walking, resonance traversal, or structural intuition unless expressed as algorithms with polynomial-time proof and correct target problem framing

& [SupportNeeds] is required support for canonical work
  = need: exact problem statement and target class
  = need: algorithmic complexity proof for any constructive traversal claim
  = need: distinguish computing digits of pi from NP-complete decision-problem resolution unless a rigorous reduction is supplied
